    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Feature description\n\nCurrently, while using both `laststatus=3` and `winbar`, there are two horizontal separators (`winbar` and `fillchars`).\r\n\r\nCause `winbar` already acts as horizontal separators like `laststatus=2`, these `fillchars` (`horiz`, `horizup`, `horizdown`) are needless.\r\n\r\nIt would be great if there is an option to remove these `fillchars` or they just disabled automatically when both `laststatus=3` and `winbar` are enabled.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1032\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60088301/193958382-8f3c89cd-8fc7-45cd-ad3f-2d0aefa18410.png\">",
